is it t shirt or tee shirt what is the proper spelling tee shirt or t shirt both are correct in every dictionary i've checked merriam webster american heritage dictionary com britanica cambridge they list both tee shirt and t shirt as acceptable however t shirt seems to have been the original spelling and tee shirt became an acceptable variation Dictionary T-shirt Noah Webster Prescription and description The American Heritage Dictionary of the English Language Encyclopedia Merriam-Webster Commonwealth English English language Spelling reform Indian English Kilt American and British English differences Crossword Tetragrammaton American and British English spelling differences County Durham Black tie Shall and will Southern United States Greek language Dictionary of American Naval Fighting Ships American English Tsar Spell checker The Warriors Spanish language Indonesian language Okay Fuck Canadian English Golf Suit (clothes) German language Dutch language Belarus Abbreviation Esperanto phonology Chauncey Allen Goodrich Baltusrol Golf Club Social aspects of clothing Cleveland, England Olympic Club River Tees Old English language Rugby league Sahalee Country Club Glossary of American football Canadian Tire Irony Afrikaans Tyne Tees Television Hangul R__maji Aluminium Clothing terminology Middlesbrough Scripps National Spelling Bee Riviera Country Club Bad-lad split German spelling reform of 1996 Modern Western square dance Mispronunciation Italian language Quechua language Fictionary Book Miwok Hot Shots Golf (series) Latin alphabet Split infinitive Romanian language Finnish language Undergarment Washington State University Tee Durham University Oxford English Dictionary Names of large numbers Shirt Formal written English - regional differences Redshirt (character) D'oh! Radical (Chinese character) Culture of the United States Breakdancing Mario International English Swiss German Dita Von Teese Boy Scouts of America Hollow Earth Kanji Cheque Dialect A Dictionary of th